Hong Kong's budget surplus for the1986/1987 fiscal year has been revised to 3.7 billion H.K. Dlrsfrom a 3.1 billion dlr estimate made in February, FinancialSecretary Piers Jacobs said.    He told the Legislative Council that the revision for theyear ended March 31, 1987 reflected higher than anticipatedstamp tax revenues due to an active stock market.    The surplus for the fiscal year was initially estimated at348 mln dlrs and was revised to 3.1 billion in Jacobs' budgetpresentation in February. The 1987/1988 budget surplus isestimated at 1.8 billion dlrs. REUTER&#3;